_vrf_PLAT201_jin87
;
PROBLEM: Isotropic non-H Atoms in Main Residue(s) .......          2 Report
RESPONSE: The C and N atoms in this structure were part of positionally 
disordered phenylethylammonium and methyl ammonium counterions. Attempts 
to refine these atoms anisotropically required the use of excessive 
restraints and constraints, and did not improve the model or results of 
refinement.
;
_vrf_PLAT420_jin87
;
PROBLEM: D-H Without Acceptor       N1       --H1B      .     Please Check 
RESPONSE: There is no acceptor atom for this H atom. 
;
_vrf_PLAT906_jin87
;
PROBLEM: Large K Value in the Analysis of Variance ......     11.309 Check 
RESPONSE: Usually data integration algorithms underestimate the background
and produces slightly elevated values of Fo, resulting in higher Fo/Fc 
values. These are most pronounced for the weakest intensities.
;
_vrf_PLAT911_jin87
;
PROBLEM: Missing FCF Refl Between Thmin & STh/L=    0.600         17 Report
RESPONSE: We believe that there is a good reason to use statistical 
analysis and if some reflections are outliers they harm rather than improve the 
refinement. The statistical analysis was conducted with program 
G4_fcf_filter published on my web site 
http://xray.chem.wisc.edu/Resources.html. 
 It uses the approach described by Prince, E., Nicholson, W.L. 
(1983) Acta Cryst A39, 407-410. For the suggested value for the 
outlier cutoff see Rollett J.S. (1988) Crystallographic Computing 
4, 149-166, Oxford University Press.
;
_vrf_PLAT971_jin87
;
PROBLEM: Check Calcd Resid. Dens.  0.70A   From I1              2.34 eA-3  
RESPONSE: The final difference Fourier map for the structure contained 
several peaks of residual electron density (ca. 2.9 e^-^/\%A^3^). 
These peaks are in chemically unreasonable positions and were considered 
noise.
;
_vrf_PLAT972_jin87
;
PROBLEM: Check Calcd Resid. Dens.  1.56A   From C4A            -4.70 eA-3  
RESPONSE: The structural model is for a set of data from a challenging 
crystal that diffracted weakly. There were indications in the data of 
multiple minor twin components; however, attempts to model the data as 
a non merohedral twin did not improve the results of refinement. 
Given this, we chose to model the data as a single crystal. In addition, 
there is extensive positional disorder present in the structure that 
required the use of restraints and constraints to ensure that the model 
was chemically reasonable. We believe that this is the best possible 
structural model achievable given these challenges.
;
_vrf_PLAT977_jin87
;
PROBLEM: Check Negative Difference Density on H1A              -0.60 eA-3  
RESPONSE: This H atom has been placed in the correct idealized position. 
Please see vrf_PLAT972 for further explanation.
;
